            <title><![CDATA[Which form of transport has the smallest carbon footprint?]]></title>
            <id>https://ourworldindata.org/travel-carbon-footprint</id>
            <link rel="alternate" href="https://ourworldindata.org/travel-carbon-footprint"/>
            <published>2020-10-13T11:00:00.000Z</published>
            <updated>2020-10-14T13:20:44.000Z</updated>
            <author><name>Hannah Ritchie</name></author>
            <summary><![CDATA[Transport accounts for almost one-quarter of global CO2 emissions. For individuals, it can be the largest part of their carbon footprint. But if you need to travel, what is the lowest-carbon way to do so? We take a look at the data.<br><br><a href="https://ourworldindata.org/travel-carbon-footprint" target="_blank"><img src="https://ourworldindata.org/app/uploads/2020/10/carbon-footprint-travel-mode-3-768x542.png"/></a>]]></summary>
